  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Sliding Window - Maximum Interactivity</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    margin: 10px;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n  }\n  input[type=number] {\n    width: 60px;\n  }\n  textarea {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 80px;\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n  }\n  button {\n    min-width: 70px;\n  }\n  label {\n    user-select:none;\n  }\n  #output, #stepInfo {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 5px;\n    height: 200px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    margin-top: 10px;\n  }\n  #windowDisplay {\n    font-weight: bold;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Sliding Window - Maximum Interactivity</h1>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>1. Input Array and Parameters</h2>\n  <label for=\"inputArray\">Enter array (comma or space separated integers):</label><br />\n  <textarea id=\"inputArray\" aria-label=\"Input array\" placeholder=\"e.g. 1 3 -1 -3 5 3 6 7\"></textarea><br/>\n\n  <label for=\"windowSize\">Window size k (integer ≥1): </label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"windowSize\" min=\"1\" value=\"3\"/>\n\n  <button id=\"loadArray\">Load Array</button>\n  <button id=\"randomArray\">Random Array</button>\n\n  <div id=\"arrayStatus\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>2. Sliding Window Controls</h2>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"currentPos\">Current Window Start Index (0-based):</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"currentPos\" min=\"0\" value=\"0\" />\n    <button id=\"goToPos\">Go</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <button id=\"prevWindow\">◀ Prev Window</button>\n    <button id=\"nextWindow\">Next Window ▶</button>\n    <button id=\"firstWindow\"><< First Window</button>\n    <button id=\"lastWindow\">Last Window >></button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <label for=\"slideAmount\">Slide window by steps: </label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"slideAmount\" min=\"1\" value=\"1\" />\n    <button id=\"slideLeft\">Slide Left ◀</button>\n    <button id=\"slideRight\">Slide Right ▶</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"autoPlayDelay\">Auto Play (ms delay): </label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"autoPlayDelay\" min=\"50\" value=\"500\" />\n    <button id=\"autoPlayForward\">▶ Auto Forward</button>\n    <button id=\"autoPlayBackward\">◀ Auto Backward</button>\n    <button id=\"autoPlayStop\">■ Stop</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"windowInfo\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <div><strong>Window Indices:</strong> <span id=\"windowIndices\"></span></div>\n    <div><strong>Window Elements:</strong> <span id=\"windowElements\"></span></div>\n    <div><strong>Maximum in Window:</strong> <span id=\"windowMax\"></span></div>\n    <div><strong>Minimum in Window:</strong> <span id=\"windowMin\"></span></div>\n    <div><strong>Sum:</strong> <span id=\"windowSum\"></span></div>\n    <div><strong>Average:</strong> <span id=\"windowAvg\"></span></div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>3. Explore Sliding Window Computation</h2>\n\n  <label for=\"functionSelect\">Function to visualize:</label>\n  <select id=\"functionSelect\" aria-label=\"Choose sliding window function\">\n    <option value=\"max\">MAXIMUM</option>\n    <option value=\"min\">MINIMUM</option>\n    <option value=\"sum\">SUM</option>\n    <option value=\"average\">AVERAGE</option>\n  </select>\n\n  <button id=\"computeAllWindows\">Compute All Windows</button>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"allWindowsScroll\">Scroll through windows:</label>\n    <input type=\"range\" id=\"allWindowsScroll\" min=\"0\" max=\"0\" value=\"0\" style=\"width:300px\" disabled />\n    <span id=\"scrollWindowIndex\">0</span>/<span id=\"scrollWindowMax\">0</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"output\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>4. Interactive Sliding Window Algorithm Simulation (MAXIMUM)</h2>\n  <p>\n    Step through the classical \"Sliding Window Maximum\" algorithm using a deque,\n    manually pushing and popping elements to understand the internal state changes.\n  </p>\n\n  <div>\n    <strong>Array:</strong>\n    <span id=\"simArrayDisplay\"></span>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <strong>Window size k:</strong> <span id=\"simWindowSize\"></span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"simIndex\">Simulation index i (0-based): </label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"simIndex\" min=\"0\" value=\"0\" disabled />\n    <button id=\"simSetIndex\" disabled>Set i</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <button id=\"simNextStep\" disabled>Next Step ▶</button>\n    <button id=\"simPrevStep\" disabled>◀ Previous Step</button>\n    <button id=\"simReset\" disabled>Reset Simulation</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <strong>Current deque state (indices):</strong>\n    <span id=\"simDeque\"></span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <strong>Current i value:</strong> <span id=\"simCurrentI\"></span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <button id=\"simPushRight\" disabled>Push i into deque</button>\n    <button id=\"simPopRight\" disabled>Pop elements &lt; current i</button>\n    <button id=\"simPopLeft\" disabled>Pop out of window front</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"stepInfo\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:15px;\"></div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:15px;\">\n    <strong>Current max for completed windows:</strong>\n    <span id=\"simOutput\"></span>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // State\n  let array = [];\n  let k = 3;\n\n  // Sliding window position\n  let currentWindowStart = 0;\n\n  // Auto play\n  let autoPlayTimer = null;\n  let autoPlayDirection = 1; // 1 forward, -1 backward\n\n  // Simulation state for sliding window maximum with deque\n  let simState = {\n    i: 0,\n    deque: [], // stores indices\n    output: [],\n    steps: [],\n    running: false,\n    maxIndex: 0,\n  };\n\n  // Elements\n  const inputArrayEl = document.getElementById(\"inputArray\");\n  const windowSizeEl = document.getElementById(\"windowSize\");\n  const loadArrayBtn = document.getElementById(\"loadArray\");\n  const randomArrayBtn = document.getElementById(\"randomArray\");\n  const arrayStatusEl = document.getElementById(\"arrayStatus\");\n\n  const currentPosEl = document.getElementById(\"currentPos\");\n  const goToPosBtn = document.getElementById(\"goToPos\");\n  const prevWindowBtn = document.getElementById(\"prevWindow\");\n  const nextWindowBtn = document.getElementById(\"nextWindow\");\n  const firstWindowBtn = document.getElementById(\"firstWindow\");\n  const lastWindowBtn = document.getElementById(\"lastWindow\");\n  const slideAmountEl = document.getElementById(\"slideAmount\");\n  const slideLeftBtn = document.getElementById(\"slideLeft\");\n  const slideRightBtn = document.getElementById(\"slideRight\");\n\n  const autoPlayDelayEl = document.getElementById(\"autoPlayDelay\");\n  const autoPlayForwardBtn = document.getElementById(\"autoPlayForward\");\n  const autoPlayBackwardBtn = document.getElementById(\"autoPlayBackward\");\n  const autoPlayStopBtn = document.getElementById(\"autoPlayStop\");\n\n  const windowIndicesEl = document.getElementById(\"windowIndices\");\n  const windowElementsEl = document.getElementById(\"windowElements\");\n  const windowMaxEl = document.getElementById(\"windowMax\");\n  const windowMinEl = document.getElementById(\"windowMin\");\n  const windowSumEl = document.getElementById(\"windowSum\");\n  const windowAvgEl = document.getElementById(\"windowAvg\");\n\n  const functionSelectEl = document.getElementById(\"functionSelect\");\n  const computeAllWindowsBtn = document.getElementById(\"computeAllWindows\");\n  const allWindowsScrollEl = document.getElementById(\"allWindowsScroll\");\n  const scrollWindowIndexEl = document.getElementById(\"scrollWindowIndex\");\n  const scrollWindowMaxEl = document.getElementById(\"scrollWindowMax\");\n  const outputEl = document.getElementById(\"output\");\n\n  // Simulation elements\n  const simArrayDisplayEl = document.getElementById(\"simArrayDisplay\");\n  const simWindowSizeEl = document.getElementById(\"simWindowSize\");\n  const simIndexEl = document.getElementById(\"simIndex\");\n  const simSetIndexBtn = document.getElementById(\"simSetIndex\");\n  const simNextStepBtn = document.getElementById(\"simNextStep\");\n  const simPrevStepBtn = document.getElementById(\"simPrevStep\");\n  const simResetBtn = document.getElementById(\"simReset\");\n  const simDequeEl = document.getElementById(\"simDeque\");\n  const simCurrentIEl = document.getElementById(\"simCurrentI\");\n  const simPushRightBtn = document.getElementById(\"simPushRight\");\n  const simPopRightBtn = document.getElementById(\"simPopRight\");\n  const simPopLeftBtn = document.getElementById(\"simPopLeft\");\n  const stepInfoEl = document.getElementById(\"stepInfo\");\n  const simOutputEl = document.getElementById(\"simOutput\");\n\n  // Utility functions\n  function parseArrayInput(str) {\n    if (!str) return [];\n    const parts = str.trim().split(/[\\s,]+/);\n    const nums = [];\n    for (const p of parts) {\n      if (p === \"\") continue;\n      const n = Number(p);\n      if (Number.isNaN(n)) return null;\n      nums.push(n);\n    }\n    return nums;\n  }\n\n  function clamp(num, min, max) {\n    return Math.min(max, Math.max(min, num));\n  }\n\n  // Validations and error reporting\n  function validateArrayAndK(arr, k) {\n    if (!Array.isArray(arr) || arr.length === 0) {\n      return \"Array must have at least one number\";\n    }\n    if (!Number.isInteger(k) || k < 1) {\n      return \"Window size k must be an integer ≥ 1\";\n    }\n    if (k > arr.length) {\n      return \"Window size k must be less or equal to array length (\" + arr.length + \")\";\n    }\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // ========== 1. Load array and parameters ===========\n  function loadArrayAndParameters() {\n    const raw = inputArrayEl.value;\n    const arr = parseArrayInput(raw);\n    const kNum = parseInt(windowSizeEl.value, 10);\n    const err = validateArrayAndK(arr, kNum);\n    if (err) {\n      arrayStatusEl.textContent = \"Error: \" + err;\n      return false;\n    }\n    array = arr;\n    k = kNum;\n    arrayStatusEl.textContent = \"Loaded array of length \" + array.length + \" with window size k = \" + k;\n    resetSlidingWindow();\n    resetSimulation();\n    updateSimulationControlsState(true);\n    updateAllWindowsOutputControlsState(false);\n    updateWindowControlsState(true);\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  loadArrayBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    loadArrayAndParameters();\n  });\n\n  randomArrayBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    let len = prompt(\"Random array length? (integer ≥1)\", \"10\");\n    len = Math.max(1, Math.min(100, parseInt(len, 10) || 10));\n    let windowSizePrompt = prompt(\"Window size k?\", \"3\");\n    windowSizePrompt = Math.max(1, Math.min(len, parseInt(windowSizePrompt,10) || 3));\n    const randomArr = [];\n    for(let i=0; i<len; ++i){\n      // Random integers from -20 to 20\n      randomArr.push(Math.floor(Math.random()*41)-20);\n    }\n    inputArrayEl.value = randomArr.join(\" \");\n    windowSizeEl.value = windowSizePrompt;\n    loadArrayAndParameters();\n  });\n\n  // ========== 2. Sliding window controls ==========\n\n  function maxWindowStartIndex() {\n    return array.length - k;\n  }\n\n  function updateSlidingWindowDisplay() {\n    if (array.length === 0) {\n      windowIndicesEl.textContent = \"\";\n      windowElementsEl.textContent = \"\";\n      windowMaxEl.textContent = \"\";\n      windowMinEl.textContent = \"\";\n      windowSumEl.textContent = \"\";\n      windowAvgEl.textContent = \"\";\n      currentPosEl.value = 0;\n      return;\n    }\n    currentWindowStart = clamp(currentWindowStart, 0, maxWindowStartIndex());\n    currentPosEl.value = currentWindowStart;\n\n    const start = currentWindowStart;\n    const end = start + k - 1;\n    windowIndicesEl.textContent = \"[\" + start + \" ... \" + end + \"]\";\n    const windowSlice = array.slice(start, start + k);\n    windowElementsEl.textContent = windowSlice.join(\", \");\n    const wmax = Math.max(...windowSlice);\n    const wmin = Math.min(...windowSlice);\n    const wsum = windowSlice.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0);\n    const wavg = (wsum/k).toFixed(3);\n    windowMaxEl.textContent = wmax;\n    windowMinEl.textContent = wmin;\n    windowSumEl.textContent = wsum;\n    windowAvgEl.textContent = wavg;\n  }\n\n  goToPosBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    let val = parseInt(currentPosEl.value,10);\n    if (Number.isNaN(val)) val=0;\n    val = clamp(val, 0, maxWindowStartIndex());\n    currentWindowStart = val;\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  prevWindowBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    currentWindowStart = Math.max(0, currentWindowStart - 1);\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  nextWindowBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    currentWindowStart = Math.min(maxWindowStartIndex(), currentWindowStart + 1);\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  firstWindowBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    currentWindowStart = 0;\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  lastWindowBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    currentWindowStart = maxWindowStartIndex();\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  slideLeftBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    let step = parseInt(slideAmountEl.value,10);\n    if (Number.isNaN(step) || step < 1) step = 1;\n    currentWindowStart = Math.max(0, currentWindowStart - step);\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  slideRightBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if(array.length===0) return;\n    let step = parseInt(slideAmountEl.value,10);\n    if (Number.isNaN(step) || step < 1) step = 1;\n    currentWindowStart = Math.min(maxWindowStartIndex(), currentWindowStart + step);\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  });\n\n  // Auto play functions\n  function autoPlayStep() {\n    if (array.length === 0) return stopAutoPlay();\n    let newPos = currentWindowStart + autoPlayDirection;\n    if (newPos < 0) newPos = 0;\n    if (newPos > maxWindowStartIndex()) newPos = maxWindowStartIndex();\n    if (newPos === currentWindowStart){\n      stopAutoPlay();\n      return;\n    }\n    currentWindowStart = newPos;\n    updateSlidingWindowDisplay();\n  }\n\n  function stopAutoPlay() {\n    if (autoPlayTimer !== null) {\n      clearInterval(autoPlayTimer);\n      autoPlayTimer = null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  autoPlayForwardBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (array.length === 0) return;\n    stopAutoPlay();\n    autoPlayDirection = 1;\n    const delay = parseInt(autoPlayDelayEl.value,10) || 500;\n    autoPlayTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      autoPlayStep();\n    }, delay);\n  });\n\n  autoPlayBackwardBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (array.length === 0) return;\n    stopAutoPlay();\n    autoPlayDirection = -1;\n    const delay = parseInt(autoPlayDelayEl.value,10) || 500;\n    autoPlayTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      autoPlayStep();\n    }, delay);\n  });\n\n  autoPlayStopBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    stopAutoPlay();\n  });\n\n  function resetSlidingWindow(){\n    currentWindowStart = 0;\n    stopAutoPlay();\n  }\n\n  // ========== 3. Explore sliding window function ============\n  // Computes the values of the function on all windows\n  // For max and min, use Math.max/Math.min; for sum/average do accordingly\n\n  // We will precompute all windows each time for interactivity\n  let allWindowsComputed = [];\n  function computeAllWindows() {\n    if (array.length === 0) {\n      outputEl.textContent = \"No array loaded.\";\n      allWindowsComputed = [];\n      allWindowsScrollEl.max = 0;\n      allWindowsScrollEl.value = 0;\n      scrollWindowIndexEl.textContent = \"0\";\n      scrollWindowMaxEl.textContent = \"0\";\n      allWindowsScrollEl.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (k > array.length) {\n      outputEl.textContent = \"Window size k greater than array length.\";\n      allWindowsComputed = [];\n      allWindowsScrollEl.max = 0;\n      allWindowsScrollEl.value = 0;\n      scrollWindowIndexEl.textContent = \"0\";\n      scrollWindowMaxEl.textContent = \"0\";\n      allWindowsScrollEl.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const func = functionSelectEl.value;\n    const n = array.length;\n    const res = [];\n    for(let start=0; start<=n-k; ++start){\n      const w = array.slice(start,start+k);\n      let val;\n      if(func === \"max\"){\n        val = Math.max(...w);\n      } else if (func === \"min\"){\n        val = Math.min(...w);\n      } else if (func === \"sum\"){\n        val = w.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0);\n      } else if (func === \"average\"){\n        val = (w.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0)/k).toFixed(3);\n      } else {\n        val = \"\";\n      }\n      res.push({start, window: w, value: val});\n    }\n    allWindowsComputed = res;\n    allWindowsScrollEl.max = res.length - 1;\n    allWindowsScrollEl.value = 0;\n    scrollWindowIndexEl.textContent = \"0\";\n    scrollWindowMaxEl.textContent = (res.length - 1).toString();\n    allWindowsScrollEl.disabled = false;\n    updateAllWindowsOutput();\n  }\n\n  function updateAllWindowsOutput() {\n    if (allWindowsComputed.length === 0) {\n      outputEl.textContent = \"No windows computed. Click Compute All Windows.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    const idx = parseInt(allWindowsScrollEl.value, 10) || 0;\n    scrollWindowIndexEl.textContent = idx.toString();\n    const win = allWindowsComputed[idx];\n    if(!win) {\n      outputEl.textContent = \"Invalid window index.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    let txt = \"\";\n    txt += `Window #${idx} [indices ${win.start} ... ${win.start+k-1}]:\\n`;\n    txt += `Elements: ${win.window.join(\", \")}\\n`;\n    txt += `Value (${functionSelectEl.value.toUpperCase()}): ${win.value}\\n\\n`;\n\n    // Additional exploration:\n    // Show running max/min/sum/average of window elements, breakdown by element\n    txt += \"Window element details:\\n\";\n    win.window.forEach((v,i) => {\n      if(functionSelectEl.value===\"max\"){\n        txt += `  Element at index ${win.start+i}: ${v} ${v === win.value ? \"(MAXIMUM)\" : \"\"}\\n`;\n      } else if(functionSelectEl.value===\"min\"){\n        txt += `  Element at index ${win.start+i}: ${v} ${v === win.value ? \"(MINIMUM)\" : \"\"}\\n`;\n      } else if(functionSelectEl.value===\"sum\"){\n        txt += `  Element at index ${win.start+i}: ${v}\\n`;\n      } else if(functionSelectEl.value===\"average\"){\n        txt += `  Element at index ${win.start+i}: ${v}\\n`;\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Show sliding window start and end and index position relative to array length\n    const percentPos = ((win.start)/(array.length - k)) * 100;\n    txt += `\\nWindow start position is ${(percentPos).toFixed(1)}% of maximum sliding range.\\n`;\n\n    outputEl.textContent = txt;\n  }\n\n  computeAllWindowsBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    computeAllWindows();\n  });\n\n  allWindowsScrollEl.addEventListener(\"input\", () => {\n    updateAllWindowsOutput();\n  });\n\n  function updateAllWindowsOutputControlsState(enabled){\n    allWindowsScrollEl.disabled = !enabled;\n  }\n\n  // ========== 4. Simulation of sliding window maximum with deque (Interactive) ==========\n\n  // States in simulation:\n  // i index ranges from 0 to array.length-1\n  // deque stores indices of elements, elements in deque are always indices to array\n  // deque is kept in decreasing order of corresponding array elements (front is maximum)\n  // we simulate stepwise:\n  // 1) remove indices from right while current element is bigger than deque's right end\n  // 2) push current i into deque (right)\n  // 3) remove indices from left if they are out of current window (i-k+1)\n  // after i >= k-1 output the element at front of deque as the window max\n\n  // We will let user control each step explicitly\n\n  function initializeSimulation(){\n    simState.i = 0;\n    simState.deque = [];\n    simState.output = [];\n    simState.steps = [];\n    simState.running = true;\n    simState.maxIndex = array.length - 1;\n    simWindowSizeEl.textContent = k.toString();\n    simArrayDisplayEl.textContent = array.join(\", \");\n    simIndexEl.min = 0;\n    simIndexEl.max = simState.maxIndex;\n    simIndexEl.value = 0;\n    simCurrentIEl.textContent = simState.i.toString();\n    simDequeEl.textContent = simState.deque.join(\", \");\n    simOutputEl.textContent = \"\";\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Simulation started. Current index i = 0.\";\n  }\n\n  function updateSimulationControlsState(enabled){\n    simIndexEl.disabled = !enabled;\n    simSetIndexBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simNextStepBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simPrevStepBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simResetBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simPushRightBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simPopRightBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    simPopLeftBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n  }\n\n  function resetSimulation() {\n    simState = {\n      i: 0,\n      deque: [],\n      output: [],\n      steps: [],\n      running: false,\n      maxIndex: array.length - 1,\n    };\n    simCurrentIEl.textContent = \"\";\n    simDequeEl.textContent = \"\";\n    simOutputEl.textContent = \"\";\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = \"\";\n  }\n\n  function refreshSimulationUI(){\n    simCurrentIEl.textContent = simState.i.toString();\n    simDequeEl.textContent = simState.deque.length ? simState.deque.join(\", \") : \"(empty)\";\n    simOutputEl.textContent = simState.output.length ? simState.output.join(\", \") : \"(none)\";\n  }\n\n  function simStepPushRight(){\n    if(simState.i > simState.maxIndex) {\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Index i out of range.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    simState.deque.push(simState.i);\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = `Pushed i = ${simState.i} to the right of deque. Deque updated.`;\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n  }\n\n  function simStepPopRight(){\n    if(simState.i > simState.maxIndex) {\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Index i out of range.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    let count = 0;\n    while(simState.deque.length > 0 && array[simState.deque[simState.deque.length - 1]] < array[simState.i]){\n      const removed = simState.deque.pop();\n      count++;\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = `Popped index ${removed} from right of deque because array[${removed}] = ${array[removed]} < array[${simState.i}] = ${array[simState.i]}`;\n    }\n    if(count === 0){\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = `No elements popped from right, as deque right is ≥ current element.`;\n    }\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n  }\n\n  function simStepPopLeft(){\n    const windowStart = simState.i - k + 1;\n    if(simState.deque.length > 0 && simState.deque[0] < windowStart){\n      const removed = simState.deque.shift();\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = `Popped index ${removed} from left of deque as it is out of current window [${windowStart} ... ${simState.i}].`;\n    } else {\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = `No elements popped from left, deque front is within current window.`;\n    }\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n  }\n\n  function simNextIndex() {\n    if(simState.i >= simState.maxIndex){\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Reached end of array.\";\n      return false;\n    }\n    simState.i++;\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = `Moved to i = ${simState.i}. Ready for next steps.`;\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  function simPrevIndex() {\n    if(simState.i <= 0){\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Already at start of array.\";\n      return false;\n    }\n    simState.i--;\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = `Moved back to i = ${simState.i}.`;\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  simSetIndexBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    let val = parseInt(simIndexEl.value,10);\n    if(val < 0) val = 0;\n    if(val > simState.maxIndex) val = simState.maxIndex;\n    simState.i = val;\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = `Index set to i = ${simState.i}`;\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n  });\n\n  simNextStepBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    simNextIndex();\n  });\n\n  simPrevStepBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    simPrevIndex();\n  });\n\n  simResetBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    initializeSimulation();\n  });\n\n  simPushRightBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    simStepPushRight();\n  });\n\n  simPopRightBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    simStepPopRight();\n  });\n\n  simPopLeftBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    simStepPopLeft();\n  });\n\n  // For advanced simulation, on i >= k-1, user may push max output\n  // Add a button for \"Add current max to output\"\n  const simAddMaxOutputBtn = document.createElement(\"button\");\n  simAddMaxOutputBtn.textContent = \"Add Current Max to Output\";\n  simAddMaxOutputBtn.disabled = true;\n  simAddMaxOutputBtn.style.marginTop = \"10px\";\n  simAddMaxOutputBtn.style.minWidth = \"160px\";\n  simAddMaxOutputBtn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (simState.i < k - 1) {\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Window not full yet. Cannot output max.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    if (simState.deque.length === 0) {\n      stepInfoEl.textContent = \"Deque empty. Cannot output max.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    const maxIdx = simState.deque[0];\n    simState.output.push(array[maxIdx]);\n    stepInfoEl.textContent = `Added array[${maxIdx}] = ${array[maxIdx]} as max for window ending at i=${simState.i}`;\n    refreshSimulationUI();\n  });\n  document.getElementById(\"stepInfo\").parentNode.appendChild(simAddMaxOutputBtn);\n\n  function updateSimAddMaxOutputBtn() {\n    if (!simState.running) {\n      simAddMaxOutputBtn.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n    if (simState.i >= k - 1 && simState.deque.length > 0) {\n      simAddMaxOutputBtn.disabled = false;\n    } else {\n      simAddMaxOutputBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Hook refreshing simAddMaxOutputBtn on each UI refresh\n  const originalRefreshUI = refreshSimulationUI;\n  refreshSimulationUI = function(){\n    originalRefreshUI();\n    updateSimAddMaxOutputBtn();\n  };\n\n  // Initialize everything on page load:\n\n  updateWindowControlsState(false);\n  updateSimulationControlsState(false);\n  updateAllWindowsOutputControlsState(false);\n\n  // Helpers to enable/disable controls\n  function updateWindowControlsState(enabled) {\n    currentPosEl.disabled = !enabled;\n    goToPosBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    prevWindowBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    nextWindowBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    firstWindowBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    lastWindowBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    slideAmountEl.disabled = !enabled;\n    slideLeftBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    slideRightBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    autoPlayDelayEl.disabled = !enabled;\n    autoPlayForwardBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    autoPlayBackwardBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n    autoPlayStopBtn.disabled = !enabled;\n  }\n\n  // ========== Initialize with a default example ===========\n  function loadDefaultExample(){\n    inputArrayEl.value = \"1 3 -1 -3 5 3 6 7\";\n    windowSizeEl.value = \"3\";\n    loadArrayAndParameters();\n  }\n\n  loadDefaultExample();\n\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
